3rd Ed:<br>
Ardeth Bey, 20th level Monk, 8th level Ninja of the Crescent Moon. He was actually supposed to be a semi-priest / temple guardian of Anubis. (Egyptian god of death, not evil, but a protector of souls in the underworld) Still not retired, raised from level 1 in a couple of campaings. My friends would do a sort of round-robin DM'ing, and we'd recycle characters quite a bit. Last campaign was Ravenloft, with a rather sadistic DM that made us fight his version of a vampire god. That specific campaign was rather munchkinish, other characters in the campaign were about my level (19 to 30th or so) and the DM really wasn't clear on my full abilities. Really fun to suprise a DM with creative uses of your abilities instead of the amount of items a character has.<br>
